cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on multi-document summarization. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as summarization is a common task in this field. The use of optimization-based methods such as determinantal point processes (DPPs) suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the mention of a similarity measure inspired by capsule networks suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as capsule networks are commonly used in image recognition tasks.
